":["From a French form of Latin <i>Laurentius</i> ‘man from Laurentum’. <i>Laurentum</i> was a town in Latium, which may have got its name from Latin <i>laurus</i> ‘laurel’, although it is more probably of pre-Roman origin. The given name was moderately popular in the Middle Ages (when it was used for girls as well as boys), under the influence of a 3rd-century saint who was one of the seven deacons of Rome. He was martyred in  258 . The legend is that, having been required to hand over the Church's treasures to the civil authorities, he assembled the poor and sick and presented them. For this act of Christian defiance, he was roasted to death on a gridiron. In England the name is also associated with  St Laurence of Canterbury  (  d. 619 ). A more recent influence has been the actor  Sir Laurence Olivier  (  1907–89 ).  See also  Lawrence ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Laurence de Montefichet was born in 1270, in Auchterarder, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Walter de Montefichet, was 44 and his mother, Margaret de Clare, was 40. He had at least 1 son with Margareta. He died in 1347, in Cargill, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1270–1347":"1270–1347","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","1280–1342":"1280–1342","1305–1366":"1305–1366","1300–1332":"1300–1332","1296–1332":"1296–1332","1226–1287":"1226–1287","1230–1295":"1230–1295","3 February 1295":"3. veebruar 1295","13 April 1342":"13. aprill 1342","1275":"1275","1230":"1230","1296":"1296","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1305":"1305","1347":"1347","1226":"1226","1300":"1300","1366":"1366","1332":"1332","1287":"1287","1342":"1342","Methven, Perthshire, Scotland":"Methven, Perthshire, Scotland","Cargill, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Cargill, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Auchterarder, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Auchterarder, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Cargill, Perthshire, Scotland":"Cargill, Perthshire, Šotimaa, Unite